.pagestyle
	.row
		.col-xs-12
			h2(style="margin-top: 0;")
				i.fa.fa-key.fa-fw
				|  SSH Keys
				small(ng-show="status.length > 0")  {{ status }}
				.pull-right.btn-group
					button.btn.btn-success(ui-sref="ssh.add") Add Public Key
					button.btn.btn-default(ng-click="generateSystemKey()") Generate System Key
	br
	.row
		.col-xs-12
			table.table
				thead
					tr
						th Name
						th Installed
						th Installing
				tbody
					tr(ng-repeat="key in keys")
						td
							a(ui-sref="ssh.edit({ key_id: key._id })") {{ key.name }}
						td {{ key.installed }}
						td {{ key.installing }}
			blockquote
				strong Pro tip:
				|  Generate &amp; Copy the "System Key" to be able to pull your code from private repositories. NodeGear will use the same key to pull ssh npm dependencies. We recommend adding the public key as a read-only deploy key to your repository.